forever and all christmas night this poem is out of season but i wrote it around christmas time and since i started cleaning out my writing box i found it i don't think i was even serious when i wrote this one sore throats fur coats and hot chocolate floats red noses white roses and warm house door closes trembling hands vast white lands and children's present demands shiv'ring kids cold forbids and ski landing skids home cooking ornament hooking and across the room looking gift wrap ripping melted snow dripping and coat hat gloves stripping gath'ring friends rival amends and an air of happiness suspends through this night light burns bright and forever and all i write really good it really feels christmassy now i'm wearing ugg boots because i broke my toe some of the best stuff we write or paint comes when we just mess around and not especially try i really like this there are hardly any rhyming stretches and you really captured the essence of the season great rhyming and hope you find more treasures like this in your writing box Happy Tree Friends Customs and etiquette of Japan Characters in the Smurfs Santa Claus Comanche Christmas Care Bears RuneScape quests Saint Nicholas Sin City Japanese tea ceremony Dr. Seuss SpongeBob SquarePants The Amber Spyglass Christmas tree Rent (musical) Wok The Cat in the Hat Cat Labrador Retriever Futurama (TV series - season 5) AFI 100 Years series Codename: Kids Next Door Dean Koontz The Care Bears (television series) One Piece minor characters In-N-Out Burger Solar power The Smoking Room Skateboarding trick The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy Pysanka Cuisine of Denmark Lighting Black tie Boxing Shaggy dog story Nursery rhyme Professional wrestling throws The Diary of Anne Frank (film) Clothing The Star Wars Holiday Special Shawn Michaels Doug Suplex Rocket Power Shen Gong Wu Frosty the Snowman Episodes of Lost (Season 2) Winter RuneScape skills RuneScape locations The Shining (film) Professional wrestling match types Tea Harr